I was extremely happy that we chose Cool Cuts 4 Kids for my son's first big boy hair cut.
He was instantly comfortable and drawn in by all of the friendly things they have for children.
He was given the choice of a movie or playing a video game, of course knowing exactly what he wants went straight for the video game (Sonic on XBOX).
It was pretty much a breeze from that point the little guy was hypnotized and didn't even realize what was going on w/ his beautiful, lovely long hair =( obviously they need to focus on distracting the mom's lol!
Jessie who cut my sons long hair was a doll, she didn't seem to be bothered by the mother breathing down her neck as she hacked off my little's hair or the boyfriend taking a copious amount of pictures and video of the whole event.
In the end my son looked great and I was a happy mama, I couldn't have asked for a better experience.

I am extraordinarily disappointed with the recent service my daughter and I have received at Cool Cuts recently.
We have been loyal customers for a long time, but are now considering taking our business elsewhere.
On our most recent visit, I arrived and was told they had no record of an appointment for us.
I had made the appointment a mere 4 hours before at that location, and it was confirmed by an employee on the phone.
On on our previous visit, despite again having a confirmed appointment, we were forced to wait 30 minutes before being seen.
This is ridiculous.

